This commissioned artwork captures a lighthearted yet gentle scene between two characters standing together in their school uniforms. One figure carries a playful presence with bunny ears and a relaxed stance, while the other stands with composed confidence, exuding calm charm. The contrast between them feels natural, like two very different personalities who still share an easy bond.

I really enjoyed bringing this moment to life, and I love how it carries both warmth and a touch of humor. Since this is a commissioned piece, it means a lot to me to hear how it makes others feel too. Does it make you smile, or maybe remind you of a friendship of your own? I would love to hear your thoughts.

What if the greatest masterpieces in history are not just art... but messages from another world? We've been told one version of history, but the evidence for a different, more shocking story has been hiding in plain sight for centuries.

Welcome to a journey into forbidden history. In this episode, we're pulling back the canvas on Leonardo da Vinci, revealing the secret codes and hidden messages in masterpieces like the Mona Lisa. Could his legendary genius have been influenced by an extraterrestrial encounter in a mysterious cave? We’ll then travel from the famous museums of Europe to the ancient world, decoding the strange, helmeted "spacemen" in the Val Camonica rock carvings and investigating the Gosford Glyphs—Egyptian hieroglyphs found in Australia that seem to depict a UFO.

This isn't just a collection of unexplained mysteries; it's a pattern. From Greek myths to Renaissance art, the fingerprints of ancient astronauts are everywhere.

Stay until the very end, because we reveal the one symbol Da Vinci hid in plain sight across multiple works that could change history forever.
Ready to see the past with new eyes? Subscribe, share this with anyone who loves a good mystery, and let us know which piece of evidence blows your mind.
